@Implementation
Reads wpa.dce_plan at WPA offset 128, then dead_types at DCEPlan offset 32.
At the given index, retrieves the type ID. Records it in CMO's
optimization_stats Dict for the type-table-pruning step at codegen time.

Returns 1 if recorded, 0 on no-op.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) Dictionary write.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
A type used by reachable code but marked dead would cause type-table
lookup failures at codegen. Soundness is WPA's responsibility.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "apply_dce_dead_type" that takes cmo as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Let wpa be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 0
    If wpa is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dce_plan be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with wpa, 128
    If dce_plan is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dead_types be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with dce_plan, 32
    If dead_types is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dead_count be proc length from List with dead_types
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to dead_count:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let type_id be proc get from List with dead_types, index

    Let stats be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 96
    If stats is not equal to 0:
        Note: Negate key to distinguish from dead-global records in the same Dict.
        Note: Type IDs and global IDs share a numeric namespace; flipping sign
        Note: gives us a collision-free 2-channel record in one Dict.
        Let type_key be 0 minus type_id
        proc set from Dictionary with stats, type_key, 1
    End If

    Let opts_applied be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 64
    Set opts_applied to opts_applied bitwise_or OPT_DCE
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cmo, 64, opts_applied

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
apply_constant_propagation_candidate applies a single constant propagation
identified by index into wpa.constant_prop_candidates.

Bucket 0x0007 dispatches here. The candidate format is the 24-byte CP
candidate struct from design section 7: value_id(0), constant_value(8),
context_function(16). Replaces all uses of value_id in context_function
with constant_value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads wpa.constant_prop_candidates at WPA offset 152 (added by Layer 1).
At the given index, retrieves the candidate struct. Then calls the
existing replace_constant_uses machinery on a single (value_id,
constant_value) tuple within the context function.

Returns 1 if at least one use was replaced, 0 if no uses found or index
out of range.

We do not have a one-shot per-tuple replace_constant_uses; the existing
implementation walks every function. For per-candidate dispatch we
narrow the scan to the candidate's context_function via a local loop.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(|context_function_instructions|) per candidate. Each use replacement
is a single memory_set_int64.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Substituting a non-constant value would break SSA correctness. WPA's
constant identification is the trust boundary; this wrapper just performs
the mechanical substitution.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "apply_constant_propagation_candidate" that takes cmo as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Let wpa be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 0
    Let mir be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 8
    If wpa is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mir is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cp_candidates be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with wpa, 152
    If cp_candidates is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let candidate_count be proc length from List with cp_candidates
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to candidate_count:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let candidate be proc get from List with cp_candidates, index
    If candidate is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let value_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with candidate, 0
    Let constant_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with candidate, 8
    Let context_function_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with candidate, 16

    Note: Locate context function in mir.functions
    Let functions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with mir, 0
    If functions is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let function_count be proc length from List with functions
    Let target_func be 0
    Let fi be 0
    While fi is less than function_count:
        Let func be proc get from List with functions, fi
        If func is not equal to 0:
            Let fid be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with func, 0
            If fid is equal to context_function_id:
                Set target_func to func
                Set fi to function_count
            End If
        End If
        Set fi to fi plus 1
    End While

    If target_func is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Walk the target function's instructions and replace uses of value_id
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with target_func, 8
    If cfg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cfg, 16
    Let block_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cfg, 24

    Let replaced_count be 0
    Let b be 0
    While b is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc get from List with blocks, b
        If block is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block, 16
            Let inst_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with block, 24
            Let ii be 0
            While ii is less than inst_count:
                Let inst be proc get from List with instructions, ii
                If inst is not equal to 0:
                    Note: Instructions store operands at offsets 16, 24, 32.
                    Note: Check each and substitute value_id -> constant_value.
                    Let op0 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 16
                    If op0 is equal to value_id:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with inst, 16, constant_value
                        Set replaced_count to replaced_count plus 1
                    End If
                    Let op1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 24
                    If op1 is equal to value_id:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with inst, 24, constant_value
                        Set replaced_count to replaced_count plus 1
                    End If
                    Let op2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with inst, 32
                    If op2 is equal to value_id:
                        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with inst, 32, constant_value
                        Set replaced_count to replaced_count plus 1
                    End If
                End If
                Set ii to ii plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Set b to b plus 1
    End While

    If replaced_count is greater than 0:
        Let prop_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 40
        Set prop_count to prop_count plus replaced_count
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cmo, 40, prop_count

        Let opts_applied be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 64
        Set opts_applied to opts_applied bitwise_or OPT_CONST_PROP
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cmo, 64, opts_applied
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
apply_specialization_candidate applies a single specialization identified
by index into wpa.specialization_candidates.

Bucket 0x0008 dispatches here. The candidate format is the 32-byte
SpecCandidate struct from design section 7: callee_id(0),
const_args_pattern(8), call_frequency(16), benefit_score(24). Creates a
specialized clone of callee_id parameterized on const_args_pattern.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads wpa.specialization_candidates at WPA offset 160 (added by Layer 1).
At the given index, retrieves the candidate. Calls the existing
create_specialized_functions machinery wrapped for a single candidate.

For the bootstrap-phase implementation, we build a single-entry Dictionary
from (callee_id -> const_args_pattern) and pass it to
create_specialized_functions; the returned count tells us whether
specialization actually happened.

Returns 1 on successful specialization, 0 on no-op.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Specialization cost is bounded by callee function body size (one clone
plus parameter rewriting). For per-candidate dispatch, allocates a
transient single-entry Dictionary which is destroyed at the end.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Specialized clones must preserve callee semantics for the specialized
argument pattern. WPA's analysis identified the pattern; this wrapper
trusts the analysis.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "apply_specialization_candidate" that takes cmo as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Let wpa be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 0
    Let mir be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 8
    If wpa is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mir is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let spec_candidates be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with wpa, 160
    If spec_candidates is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let candidate_count be proc length from List with spec_candidates
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to candidate_count:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let candidate be proc get from List with spec_candidates, index
    If candidate is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with candidate, 0
    Note: SpecCandidate layout (whole_program_analysis.runa:allocate_spec_candidate):
    Note:   offset 0:  function_id
    Note:   offset 8:  caller_count
    Note:   offset 16: benefit
    Note:   offset 24: dominant_const_arg (parameter index, or -1 if no dominant)
    Note: The specialization seed is the dominant_const_arg at offset 24 — that
    Note: is the parameter position the WPA identified as constant across at
    Note: least 75% of call sites. Convert it to the 64-bit pattern bitmask
    Note: that create_specialized_functions consumes.
    Let dominant_arg be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with candidate, 24
    If dominant_arg is less than 0:
        Note: WPA found no dominant constant parameter; nothing to specialize on.
        Return 0
    End If
    Let const_args_pattern be 1 shifted left by dominant_arg

    Note: Build single-entry Dict for create_specialized_functions consumption.
    Let single_entry be proc create from Dictionary
    If single_entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc set from Dictionary with single_entry, callee_id, const_args_pattern

    Let specialized_count be create_specialized_functions(mir, single_entry)
    proc destroy from Dictionary with single_entry

    If specialized_count is greater than 0:
        Let opts_applied be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 64
        Set opts_applied to opts_applied bitwise_or OPT_SPECIALIZE
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with cmo, 64, opts_applied
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
optimize_merged_program_prioritized is the O3 priority-driven dispatcher.
Replaces the fixed-order CMO pipeline (optimize_merged_program +
apply_all_optimizations) with a priority-ordered traversal of
wpa.optimization_priorities.

Per design section 3.5.3: keys in the priority Dict are bucket-tagged
op_ids (high 16 bits = bucket, low 48 bits = candidate index). Each entry
is dispatched to the appropriate per-bucket apply wrapper. The order
matters: applying specialization before DCE can leave dead clones, etc.,
so the WPA-computed priority order is treated as authoritative.

This replaces section 3.5.3's pseudo-code Match statement with the
expanded If/Otherwise chain (the v0.0.8.5 bootstrap stage1 parser does
not yet accept Match with integer literal patterns reliably).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads wpa.optimization_priorities (WPA offset 136). Calls
sort_priority_dict_descending to get a sorted List of op_ids. Iterates,
decoding bucket and index, dispatches to the appropriate apply wrapper.

If priorities is null or empty (Layer 1 has not populated it yet for any
of the buckets), this Process falls back to the fixed-order O2 pipeline
so that O3 builds do not silently skip all LTO. This is a defensive
behavior; once Layer 1 ships, the fallback should never trigger.

Returns the total number of candidates that returned 1 from their dispatch.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Sort cost is O(n log n) where n is total candidate count. Dispatch is
O(n) with per-candidate cost dominated by the underlying apply wrapper.
For a 10k-function program with ~100 candidates total, total dispatch
cost is well under 10ms.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Compile-time only. The priority order influences codegen quality but
not correctness; every per-bucket wrapper has the same soundness
guarantee as in the fixed-order path.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "optimize_merged_program_prioritized" that takes cmo as Integer returns Integer:
    Let wpa be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with cmo, 0
    If wpa is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let priorities be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with wpa, 136

    Note: If priorities is unpopulated, fall back to O2 fixed-order pipeline.
    Note: This keeps O3 builds correct in the window between Layer 2 landing
    Note: and Layer 1 finishing compute_optimization_priorities population.
    If priorities is equal to 0:
        optimize_merged_program(cmo)
        apply_all_optimizations(cmo)
        Return 1
    End If

    Let priority_size be proc size from Dictionary with priorities
    If priority_size is equal to 0:
        optimize_merged_program(cmo)
        apply_all_optimizations(cmo)
        Return 1
    End If

    Let sorted_ops be sort_priority_dict_descending(priorities)
    If sorted_ops is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let n be proc length from List with sorted_ops
    Let applied_total be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n:
        Let op_id be proc get from List with sorted_ops, i
        Let bucket be (op_id shifted right by BUCKET_SHIFT) bitwise and BUCKET_MASK
        Let index be op_id bitwise and INDEX_MASK

        Let applied_one be 0
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_INLINING:
            Set applied_one to apply_inlining_candidate(cmo, index)
        End If
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_DEVIRT_EXACT:
            Set applied_one to apply_devirt_candidate_exact(cmo, index)
        End If
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_DEVIRT_SPECULATIVE:
            Set applied_one to apply_devirt_candidate_speculative(cmo, index)
        End If
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_DCE_DEAD_FUNCTION:
            Set applied_one to apply_dce_dead_function(cmo, index)
        End If
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_DCE_DEAD_GLOBAL:
            Set applied_one to apply_dce_dead_global(cmo, index)
        End If
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_DCE_DEAD_TYPE:
            Set applied_one to apply_dce_dead_type(cmo, index)
        End If
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_CONSTANT_PROPAGATION:
            Set applied_one to apply_constant_propagation_candidate(cmo, index)
        End If
        If bucket is equal to BUCKET_SPECIALIZATION:
            Set applied_one to apply_specialization_candidate(cmo, index)
        End If

        If applied_one is equal to 1:
            Set applied_total to applied_total plus 1
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: After priority-driven candidate apply, run the bulk sweep / verify /
    Note: measure / finalize phases that apply_all_optimizations would run.
    Note: These are idempotent on already-applied candidates.
    Let is_correct be verify_optimization_correctness(cmo)
    If is_correct is equal to 0:
        rollback_unsafe_optimizations(cmo)
    End If
    measure_optimization_impact(cmo)
    finalize_optimized_program(cmo)

    proc destroy from List with sorted_ops

    Return applied_total
End Process
